de.ryanthara.ja.rycon.data

Class I18N

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.ryanthara.ja.rycon.data.I18N

  • public class I18N
extends java.lang.Object
    This class implements multi-language support to RyCON.

    In the first version of RyCON there are support for the following languages.

    • english - since version 1
    • german - since version 1
    • ...

    Every translated text in the program is prepared as String object here. The singular and plural words are controlled with parameters.

    Because of the fact that there are a lot of user who has java version 6 or 7 running, RyCON uses no functions of java version 8 in versions lower than 2.

    Since:
    1
    Version:
    1
    Author:
    sebastian

      • prepareString

        private static java.lang.String prepareString(java.lang.String property,
                                              boolean singular)
        Helper for string preparation to differ between singular and plural text.

        In the properties file the String "§§" is used as delimiter. The values for singular is set with Main.TEXT_SINGULAR and for plural is set with Main.TEXT_PLURAL

        Parameters:
        property - property to get the text from
        singular - set to get a singular or plurar text back
        Returns:
        singular or plural string message
